<br>
On OTHER servers, they actually take a fairly lax view of the whole thing, depending on the GM staff.  Since FV is actually billed as the role-play server, the GMs here seem to take VI’s stated policy a little more seriously.<br>
<br>
“The Turtles” probably would never have been nixed on, say, Prexus, I’ll wager.  Here, on the server that Verant ostensibly created for the enjoyment of people who like to be a little more fully immersed in the fantasy, they removed what was a pretty obvious parody.<br>
<br>
Again, the person that petitioned did nothing.  The GMs were alerted to the names, evaluated them and decided they violated the policy.  If this (alleged) person had not petitioned now, they would have simply had a stay of execution, not permission to continue.<br>
<br>
There is also the possibility that there is no petitioner.  The GM who changed their name may have just made that up so that he would not have to listen to the turtle’s complaints as he implemented Verant’s policy.  Unlikely, I’ll grant, since the GMs don’t usually have any issue with saying what they mean, but possible.<br>
<br>
